==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tantalum
<hw>Tan"ta*lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. So named on
account of the perplexity and difficulty encounterd by its discoverer
(Ekeberg) in isolating it. See <er>Tantalus</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A rare nonmetallic element found in certain
minerals, as tantalite, samarskite, and fergusonite, and isolated as a
dark powder which becomes steel-gray by burnishing. Symbol Ta. Atomic
weight 182.0. Formerly called also
<altname>tantalium</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tantalus</ent>⟦br⟧
